Definition: the theological doctrine put forward by Pelagius which denied original sin and affirmed the ability of humans to be righteous
Example: condemned as heresy by the Council of Ephesus in 431
Synonyms: theological_doctrine, heresy, the, theological, doctrine, put, forward, by, Pelagius, which, denied, original, sin, and, affirmed, ability, of, humans, to, be, righteous, condemned, as, Council, Ephesus, in
Category: noun.cognition
